subject: tqm7vje80tbdkbb
reason: You are looking for me to give a naturalistic reason for my choice. You want me to rationalise my choice to you in that manner. Then there is also the precedent argument, its is  social norm in almost all societies, through nearly all of time, not to eat flesh, and especially not dead flesh. It only appears in small scale sub groups and is often linked to power and control. Therefore, without recourse to any naturalistic arguments, precedent would seem to indicate it is negative, and niche. Thus, it is wrong. However, the argument here does not even need to rely on precedent, anthropological, sociological, or otherwise. Rather, in today's world you can be fired, fined, ostracised, arrested, jailed etc for one misplaced comment. This is not an exaggeration, there are numerous cases that most everyone alive will be aware of such is the narcissistic, and neurotic, nature of our times. That being said, if this is true, and it is, then a if misplaced comment should provoke such punishment, the the eating of human flesh must rank as one of the most heinous liberties in all of human experience,............. no? ;)
